<!DOCTYPE html>
<html class="h-full">
  <head>
    <%= render 'layouts/common_header' %>
  </head>

  <body class="h-full bg-pink-50">
    <article class="min-h-full flex flex-col align-stretch">
      <header class="px-5 py-6 sm:py-8 bg-wiggle bg-green-800 flex-shrink-0">
	<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto flex items-center justify-between">
	  <%= link_to root_path do %>
	    <h1 class="text-pink-300 font-display text-2xl sm:text-4xl">Chore Pig</h1>
	  <% end %>
	  <% if user_signed_in? %>
	    <%= link_to 'Account', edit_user_registration_path, class: "rounded-full bg-pink-600 px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-pink-100 shadow-sm hover:bg-pink-700 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-pink-300" %>
	  <% else %>
	    <%= link_to 'Sign in', new_user_session_path, class: "rounded-full bg-pink-600 px-2.5 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-pink-100 shadow-sm hover:bg-pink-700 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-pink-600" %>
	  <% end %>

	</div>
      </header>
      <main class="flex-1 flex-shrink-0 container mx-auto max-w-7xl mt-16 sm:px-5 flex flex-col">
	<%= image_tag "pig.png", alt: 'Pig', class: "-mt-28 sm:-mt-36 mb-4 mx-auto inline-block h-24 w-24 sm:h-40 sm:w-40 rounded-full ring-4 border border-pink-100 ring-pink-50" %>
	<noscript>
	  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl w-full py-12 space-y-2">
	    <p>Hey there, bucko!</p>
	    <p>You're browsing this page without javascript enabled. That's totally fine! I often like browsing the web without javascript enabled, as well.</p>
	    <p>However, Chore Pig will not work for you without Javascript enabled. Not because we've built some fancy SPA, ignoring equally powerful non-js alternatives.</p>
	    <p>No, Chore Pig needs javascript to do lots of things that are just not possible without it. Things such as storing data in IndexedDB.</p>
	    <p>If you wanna give us a shot, enable javascript and refresh the page, but we also understand if it's not a good match.</p>
	  </div>
	</noscript>
	<div id="root" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl w-full py-12">
	</div>
	<input type="hidden" id="loggedIn" name="loggedIn" value="<%= user_signed_in? %>"/>
      </main>
      <%= render 'layouts/footer' %>
    </article>
    <%= render 'layouts/flash' %>
  </body>
</html>
